The paper deals with the stable marriage problem, which is a classic problem in game theory and algorithmic game theory. The focus is on the partial information setting, which is a topic of interest in both computer science and economics. The paper also discusses approximation algorithms and hardness of approximation, which are common themes in theoretical computer science. Therefore, the most likely sub-category is cs.GT (Computer Science and Game Theory). Other likely sub-categories include cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) due to the use of algorithms and optimization techniques, cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms) due to the focus on approximation algorithms, cs.SI (Social and Information Networks) due to the study of matching markets, and cs.LG (Machine Learning) due to the use of optimization techniques.
